      "Hair and make-up are essential components of visual storytelling in film and television,\nshaping character, period, genre, and realism on screen. This course is delivered as a\nspecialist pathway within the Pearson BTEC Higher National Diploma in Hair and Make-Up\nArtistry, with a clear focus on professional practice for film and television production.\nGrounded in Pearson\u2019s nationally recognised qualification framework, the programme\ndevelops core skills in hair styling, make-up application, prosthetics, and special effects,\nwhile contextualising learning specifically for screen-based work. Students explore how\nhair and make-up support narrative, character development, and continuity across a range\nof production contexts.",
    keyInformation:
      "This course is designed for aspiring hair and make-up artists who want to specialise in film and television production.\nIt is particularly suited to students interested in character-led make-up, period hair and make-up, prosthetics, special effects, and continuity for screen. The pathway supports those who wish to work within film, television, streaming, and independent production environments.\nAligned with Raindance\u2019s ethos of empowering independent creators, the course encourages students to combine creative skill with professional discipline, preparing them to work confidently within the fast-paced realities of screen production.\nSpecial effects (SFX) make-up forms an integral part of this course and is taught alongside core hair and make-up artistry skills. Students are introduced to professional techniques used to create character transformations, injuries, ageing effects, fantasy and creature looks for film and television.",
    overview:
      "Drawing on Raindance\u2019s long-standing position at the heart of independent film culture, the\ncourse reflects real-world production environments. Students work closely with\nfilmmakers, actors, costume designers, and production teams, gaining practical experience\nof how hair and make-up departments operate within professional film and television\nproductions.\nBy the end of the programme, students will have developed a professional hair and make-up\nportfolio and the industry awareness required to pursue careers in hair and make-up\nartistry, prosthetics, and special effects for film and television, or to progress to a one-year\nBA Honours top-up degree.",
