    structure:
      "Professional practice is at the heart of this course. You will create industry-relevant digital artefacts\u2014from playable game prototypes and animated shorts to professional VFX sequences\u2014as the main focus of your learning and assessment.\nStudents choose a specialisation\u2014Games Development, Animation, or Visual Effects\u2014and refine their creative, technical, and research skills through a combination of project work, academic study, and professional development.\nYou\u2019ll work on independent and collaborative projects, explore the business and production aspects of digital media, and benefit from guest lectures, workshops, and one-on-one mentoring from industry professionals.\nSEMESTER 1\nModule 1: Critical Research (15 credits)\nInvestigate a topic related to your chosen specialisation\u2014such as animation theory, gameplay design, or compositing techniques\u2014through academic and practical research. You\u2019ll develop skills in critical analysis, research design, and reflective practice, culminating in a written or visual research output that informs your final project.\nModule 2: Specialist Negotiated Practical Project (45 credits)\nDesign and deliver a self-directed creative project based on your interests and career ambitions. This could include a playable game prototype, a short animated sequence, or a VFX compositing reel. You\u2019ll manage the full creative process\u2014from concept development and pre-production through to final output\u2014supported by workshops and tutorials.\nYour final submission will include your completed project, a process journal, and a critical evaluation of your creative workflow.\nSEMESTER 2\nModule 3: Film & TV Business Practices (15 credits)\nGain essential knowledge of the games, animation, and VFX industries, including studio workflows, job roles, production management, and intellectual property. You\u2019ll study real-world business models, funding structures, and career strategies. Assessment may take the form of a case study, industry report, or video presentation exploring your chosen career pathway.\nModule 4: Final Project \u2013 Film Practices (45 credits)\nThis is your opportunity to create a portfolio-quality project within your chosen specialism. Options include:\nGames: Developing a playable game prototype using Unreal Engine or Unity\nAnimation: Producing a short 2D or 3D animated film\nVisual Effects: Creating a professional composited VFX sequence integrated with live action\nYou will lead the full production process\u2014from concept and design to post-production and presentation\u2014showcasing advanced creative and technical skills. The final submission includes your finished artefact, documentation of your pipeline and workflow, and a critical reflection suitable for professional presentation or festival submission.",
